      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) reported for hemolysis-relevant quantities (shear stress, velocity gradients) across at least three mesh refinement levels.",
      "rationale": "GCI study performed on only two mesh levels due to computational resource constraints; Richardson extrapolation cannot be formally applied. The GCI estimate is therefore unreliable, placing achieved level at 1, below the required level 2. The team noted the coarse-to-medium mesh change in RH index was less than 4% and accepted the result without formal three-level convergence evidence."
    },
    {
