      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (shear stress, exposure time, hemolysis index) are directly linked to the COU decision criterion (RH < 1).",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI — relative hemolysis index — is the regulatory acceptance criterion for CPB device comparison against predicate. Secondary QoIs (wall shear stress distributions, particle residence time) are physically linked to the power-law hemolysis model inputs."
